ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: definitely good for improving language ability constantly

I would recommend this class just as it was recommended to me last year by the DGS of the history department. It is vital for a non-native English speaker to get prepared to teach in English, especially in the humanities, and the course addresses the challenges posed by this.
I strongly recommend this class to whom does not has teaching experience in English.
People who need to be a TA are recommended to take it, especially those whose mother tone is not English
